==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Saccharone
<hw>Sac"cha*rone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Sacchar</ets>in + lact<ets>one</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A white crystalline substance,
<chform>C6H8O6</chform>, obtained by the oxidation of saccharin, and
regarded as the lactone of saccharonic acid.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>An
oily liquid, <chform>C6H10O2</chform>, obtained by the reduction of
saccharin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saccharonic</ent>⟦br⟧
